  <issue-list>
    <issue id="1" title="FileContentsFlags::DATA missing" status="fixed">
      <description>
        The code uses `FileContentsFlags::DATA`, but the upstream `ironrdp-cliprdr` crate no longer exposes this associated constant. The build error suggests the constant does not exist in the current scope. Upstream may have renamed or removed it, or a different version is being resolved.
      </description>
      <files>src/clipboard/manager.rs (lines 984, 2198, 3099)</files>
      <docs>
        <link>https://docs.rs/ironrdp-cliprdr/0.5.0/ironrdp_cliprdr/pdu/struct.FileContentsFlags.html</link>
        <link>https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Devolutions/IronRDP/d0e18e3693f313e83c769fb37fa991965d2a39d3/crates/ironrdp-cliprdr/src/pdu/file_contents.rs</link>
        <note>The `FileContentsFlags::DATA` constant exists in version 0.5.0 but may have been removed in the git master branch.</note>
      </docs>
      <resolution>
        Replaced `FileContentsFlags::DATA` with `FileContentsFlags::RANGE` in all three locations (lines 984, 2198, 3099).
        The upstream IronRDP split the DATA flag into SIZE and RANGE. All three usages were requesting actual file data content,
        not just metadata, so RANGE is the correct flag.
        Commit: 2d69ca2
      </resolution>
    </issue>
    <issue id="2" title="ClipboardMessage::SendLockClipboard variant removed" status="fixed">
      <description>
        The enum `ironrdp_cliprdr::backend::ClipboardMessage` no longer contains a `SendLockClipboard` variant. The build fails where this variant is constructed. Upstream likely restructured clipboard message handling.
      </description>
      <files>src/clipboard/manager.rs (lines 2025, 2123)</files>
      <docs>
        <link>https://docs.rs/ironrdp-cliprdr/0.5.0/ironrdp_cliprdr/backend/enum.ClipboardMessage.html</link>
        <link>https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Devolutions/IronRDP/d0e18e3693f313e83c769fb37fa991965d2a39d3/crates/ironrdp-cliprdr/src/backend.rs</link>
        <link>https://docs.rs/ironrdp-cliprdr/0.1.1/src/ironrdp_cliprdr/backend.rs.html#10-22</link>
        <note>The enum variants in the latest upstream version are: `SendInitiateCopy`, `SendFormatData`, `SendInitiatePaste`, and `Error`.</note>
      </docs>
      <resolution>
        Removed the two usages of `ClipboardMessage::SendLockClipboard` (lines 2020-2028 and 2112-2126 in manager.rs).
        The upstream IronRDP (CliprdrServer) automatically sends Lock/Unlock PDUs when file data is detected in FormatList PDUs
        per [MS-RDPECLIP] spec. Manual Lock PDU sending from the backend is no longer supported or necessary.
        The `clip_data_id` variable is still retained as it's used for FUSE file management and file tracking.
        Build verification: `cargo build --release --features "vsock,gui,wayland,wl-clipboard,libei"` - SendLockClipboard error no longer appears.
        Commit: bdba18f
      </resolution>
    </issue>
    <issue id="3" title="Index type mismatch (u32 vs i32) in clipboard manager" status="fixed">
      <description>
        Several places pass a `u32` where the upstream API now expects an `i32` for file indices. This appears in the construction of `FileContentsRequest` and `FileContentsResponse`.
      </description>
      <files>src/clipboard/manager.rs (lines 983, 2179, 3082)</files>
      <docs>
        <link>https://docs.rs/ironrdp-cliprdr/0.5.0/ironrdp_cliprdr/pdu/struct.FileContentsRequest.html</link>
        <link>https://docs.rs/ironrdp-cliprdr/0.5.0/ironrdp_cliprdr/pdu/struct.FileContentsResponse.html</link>
        <link>https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Devolutions/IronRDP/d0e18e3693f313e83c769fb37fa991965d2a39d3/crates/ironrdp-cliprdr/src/pdu/file_contents.rs</link>
      </docs>
      <resolution>
        Changed index field from u32 to i32 in three FileContentsRequest constructions:
        - Line 983: `index: request.file_index` -> `index: request.file_index as i32` (request.file_index is u32 from fuse::FileContentsRequest)
        - Line 2179: `index: idx as u32` -> `index: idx as i32` (idx is usize from enumerate())
        - Line 3082: `index: file_index` -> `index: file_index as i32` (file_index is u32 from IncomingFile struct)
        Per MS-RDPECLIP spec referenced in upstream source, lindex is a signed 32-bit integer.
        Build verification: `cargo build --release --features "vsock,gui,wayland,wl-clipboard,libei"` - Index type mismatch errors no longer appear.
      </resolution>
    </issue>
    <issue id="4" title="CliprdrBackend trait version conflict" status="fixed">
      <description>
        The error indicates multiple versions of `ironrdp-cliprdr` in the dependency graph (0.5.0 from crates.io and git master). The `RdpCliprdrBackend` implements a different version of `CliprdrBackend` than expected by the upstream server code. This requires aligning the `ironrdp-cliprdr` version used across all dependencies.
      </description>
      <files>Cargo.toml (IronRDP dependencies), src/clipboard/ironrdp_backend.rs (line 250)</files>
      <docs>
        <link>https://docs.rs/ironrdp-cliprdr/0.5.0/ironrdp_cliprdr/backend/trait.CliprdrBackend.html</link>
        <link>https://docs.rs/ironrdp-cliprdr/latest/ironrdp_cliprdr/backend/trait.CliprdrBackend.html</link>
        <link>https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Devolutions/IronRDP/d0e18e3693f313e83c769fb37fa991965d2a39d3/crates/ironrdp-cliprdr/src/backend.rs</link>
